race.comment: BETTA BEING SINGLE (4) impressively shed the maiden tag at Ipswich last time out and will have derived a stack of confidence from that breakthrough victory. Winning rider Huxtable stays on top and should be going very close again. BRUTAL BOWLER (1) had been plying his trade in tougher NSW contests before the spell and should find this assignment much more to his liking. Is one from one around this circuit and looms as the main danger. The very well-related TIME OF MY LIFE (5) (half to 25-time G1 winner Winx) boasts a win over this track and trip and can run a race while fresh. OVER DRAFT (11) strips fitter second-up from the break and is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley. Top-three prospects. SUNLIGHT MAJESTY (2) best of the rest out of the astute Vandyke barn.
